olive oil
1 Brown Onion
1 potato
1 carrot
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet flaked almonds
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Slice onion into wedges. Cut potato and carrot into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over garlic & herb seasoning,
drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces on a second lined oven tray. Sprinkle over
Nan's special seasoning, season with salt, drizzle with olive oil and toss to
coat. Roast until tender, 15-20 minutes.
• In the last 5 minutes, add flaked almonds to the side and roast until
golden.

• While pumpkin is roasting, cut haloumi into 1cm slices.

• When veggies have 5 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook haloumi until golden
brown, 1-2 minutes each side.

• When veggies are done, add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of balsamic
vinegar and olive oil to the tray with roasted veggies. Season and toss to
coat.
• Divide roast veggie toss between bowls. Top with Nan's roasted pumpkin
and haloumi slices.
• Dollop over creamy pesto dressing. Sprinkle over almonds to serve. Enjoy!